<topic id='business_definition_ward_attendance.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Ward Attendance - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_ward_attendance">Ward Attendance</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_contact">CARE CONTACT</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_ward_attendance">Ward Attendance</xref>
 is an attendance at a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_ward">WARD</xref>
 by a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 for nursing care, where the 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 is not currently admitted to that 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_care_provider">Health Care Provider</xref>
. A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_ward_attendance">Ward Attendance</xref>
 should be recorded for only one 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nurse_or_midwife_contact">Nurse or Midwife Contact</xref>
. If the attendance is primarily for the purpose of examination or treatment by a doctor it is an 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_out-patient_attendance_consultant">Out-Patient Attendance Consultant</xref>
 and not a 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_ward_attendance">Ward Attendance</xref>
. The care is for the prevention, cure, relief or investigation because of a disease, injury, health problem or other factor affecting their health status and may include one or more 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_patient_procedure">Patient Procedures</xref>
. This includes:-  </p>
  <simpletable outputclass="simpletable table table-striped table-sm">
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>a.</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Disease (physical or mental) confirmed or suspected - inclusive of undiagnosed signs or symptoms.</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>b.</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Injury - inclusive of poisoning - confirmed or suspected.</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>c.</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Health problem e.g. prostheses or graft in situ</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>d.</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>
Other factors influencing the health status of non-sick 
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_person">PERSONS</xref>
 e.g.        </p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p> </p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>i.</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>pregnancy</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p> </p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>ii.</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>sexual and reproductive health (formerly known as family planning)</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p> </p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>iii.</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>potential donor (organ or tissue)</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p> </p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>iv.</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>potential problem requiring prophylactic (preventative) care</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p> </p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>v.</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>bereavement or other problem requiring health professional counselling</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p> </p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>vi.</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>cosmetic surgery</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p> </p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>vii.</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>other</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
  </simpletable>
  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_administrative_category">ADMINISTRATIVE CATEGORY</xref>
 of the 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 can be recorded for the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_ward_attendance">Ward Attendance</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
's 
    <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_first_attendance_code">FIRST ATTENDANCE CODE</xref>
 whether the first in a series or the only attendance should be recorded.  </p>

